AVOID THE KALE CAESAR AT ALL COSTS Disappointing Experience at This Location

I recently visited this Dig location and was thoroughly disappointed with my experience. I ordered the kale Caesar salad, but it was inedibly salty. It tasted like I was eating a whole container of salt! I was shocked and disappointed by the excessive saltiness.

The female Spanish employee who made my food at 10:50 AM was friendly, but the guy who rang me up was extremely friendly.

There were a couple of other issues that made my experience even more frustrating. The music was extremely loud, making it difficult for me to hear the employee. I would suggest lowering the music volume so that customers can communicate effectively with the staff.

Additionally, there were no labels on any of the food, which made it impossible for me to know what I was getting. I would strongly recommend considering labels on all food items to avoid confusion and ensure a better customer experience.

I've been to several other Dig locations, but this one fell far short of my expectations. The excessively salty kale Caesar, loud music, and lack of labels have ensured that I won't be returning to this location again.

Very nice and clean place.  Costumer service was great and friendly. They clearly tell you what you can get for your bowl and tell you in advice that  an extra side is extra. Food is amazing fresh, clean, and healthy options. A little pricey ($15) for bowl with no side drinks. But it‚Äôs worth it.
I love coming here. Food is always fresh and there‚Äôs a wide variety to choose from. My favorite healthy fast food option.

DIG is one of my favorite spots! I am a regular!! The food is fresh and delicious and the space is super clean.

But what truly sets this location apart is the staff. They‚Äôre more than just helpful‚Äîthey‚Äôre awesome. Friendly, upbeat, and genuinely welcoming, they create an atmosphere that makes you want to come back. It feels like they care not just about the food, but about the people who walk through the door. Today, Acosta was especially patient and kind while I figured out the DIG app‚Äîtruly above and beyond.

Highly recommend if you‚Äôre craving something wholesome and satisfying.

Got a great deal on a bogo. Food is always hot and fresh and tastes great. Hot honey chicken bowl is a must. I also love to make my own. Fast delivery service means when order comes in they are on point.

Tasty and relatively healthy choice fast casual counter service, Chipotle-like assembly line bowl meals. Fair number of choices. They do have Mac and cheese for those looking to cheat :-) It's not the biggest place and at busy times it can‚Ä¶
1st time coming here, definitely won‚Äôt be the last! Really enjoyed how fresh it was & the service was great!

I love this place! The food is fresh and delicious - loaded with carbs, veggies, and protein. Some options can be a little oily, but it‚Äôs otherwise very healthy and yummy. Would recommend to anyone looking for a quick and relatively healthy bite!

Pictured: Parmesan-toasted cauliflower, farro, roasted carrots, and roasted tofu (all great!)

Dig restaurant in NYC is a hidden gem that I stumbled upon recently, and I'm so glad I did! The food here is absolutely fantastic, with a diverse range of options that cater to various tastes and dietary preferences. Not only is the food delicious, but it's also surprisingly affordable, making it a go-to spot for those looking for a satisfying meal without breaking the bank. Whether you're a meat lover, vegetarian, or vegan, Dig has something for everyone, and each dish is prepared with care and attention to detail. If you're in the area and craving some delicious and affordable eats, I highly recommend giving Dig a try!

This is my 2nd time eating at Dig. I really like their fried chicken, tasty and well seasoned but not greasy at all. You may also try their sweet potatoes and brussel sprouts, very delicious! Will definitely come back!

The food was hot and fresh, lucky for me I came in when a fresh batch of charred chicken was done. I tried it with hot honey sauce, herb rice and it was delicious. The staff were also pleasant and the spot was clean.

Me and my girlfriend were looking for a healthy place to eat and this absolutely filled our hearts and stomachs with hearty food for an affordable price highly recommend. Servers are a little bit tired and have a slight attitude but it's not a  deterrent, I hope they're in a better mood next time because I will be back for the food and the atmosphere.

Pro: flavorful healthy foods. They have many choices of sides and main protein. The sauce is delightful.
The restroom is clean and well maintained.

Con: My only complaint is that the tofu was not hot or crispy. It would have been better taste.

The atmosphere is dope and very comfortable.

My favorite lunch spot, am literally here almost everyday! The flavor is absolutely amazing, and the steak is the bomb. All the workers there are so friendly. Karina has been the absolute best and a special shout out to Moses, thank you for the stellar food and customer service guys! üôå

I recently visited Dig Inn, and I have to say, it‚Äôs quickly become one of my favorite spots for healthy, satisfying meals. From the moment I walked in, I was impressed by the vibrant, welcoming atmosphere and the friendly staff.

The menu offers a fantastic variety of options, from perfectly seasoned roasted vegetables to flavorful proteins. My favorite go to is the Chicken, Faro and Brussel Sprouts.

Whether you‚Äôre looking for a quick bite or a nutritious meal that doesn‚Äôt skimp on flavor, Dig Inn hits the mark every time. Highly recommend giving it a try!

DIG is seriously the best! I‚Äôve been eating here a lot, and it‚Äôs been a game-changer for my gym progress. They have so many good protein options‚Äîchicken, salmon, tofu‚Äîyou name it, and everything is super fresh and actually tastes amazing. It‚Äôs hard to find a spot that‚Äôs both healthy and filling, but DIG nails it.

On top of that, the customer service is awesome. The staff is super friendly and makes you feel right at home every time you walk in. It‚Äôs just a great vibe overall. If you‚Äôre looking for a go-to spot for good food that fuels your workouts (or just your day in general), DIG is 100% the move!

Interesting food.
Ordered to take away and ate inside once. My on-site experience was nicer that to take away.
There are quite a few options, some are delicious, others are a bit less.
I wouldn't advice the salmon, overcooked in my opinion.
The mac and cheese was good, the spicy cucombers as well.

At this location, my food was ready for me to pick up. The staff looked friendly and assisted me with my order. The food was good, filling and tasty.

Got pieces/chunks of meat in my vegetarian bowl of tofu, carrots and Mac n Cheese.

I love the DiG brand and its bowls, but this branch and it‚Äôs atrocious food is a buzz kill.
Clearly they use same servicing spoons between veg and non veg pans. And they always somehow ‚Äúforget‚Äù to put sauces in your online order. So make sure you check your bag fully before take it out of store.

Please make a trip to other branches of dig, you will feel significant quality difference.

So expensive but SO good + SO high quality. This is the spot for a healthy, DELICIOUS, fast meal in NYC. All of the bowls are great - I love the kale Caesar + the carrots!! Plus you get sauces on the side. Yum!
Amazing food !!! So fresh and healthy! Workers were really nice and helpful while I was choosing what to order.

I love dig inn! It lets you to choose one base, two kinds of vegetables and one protein! Not to mention it's really affordable and good value with the amount of food you're getting. The sweet potato is to die for. Always so perfectly roasted. I can eat here everyday!

If you are looking to eat fresh and healthy food, you should definitely check this place out! The carrots are just too good, I would visit just for them. I highly recommend trying charred chicken, Jasper Hill mac, and cheese as well. Might get a little crowded during peak hours, but it is easy to find a table otherwise. Staff here are really friendly and polite.

Anyone looking for something more than a golden arch experience or an evening dining with the king eating burgers and fries check out DIG. It is as close to a home cooked dinner as you can get and that is appreciated greatly. My only gripe‚Ä¶

Got a Salmon bowl with Brown Rice, Broccoli and Mac and Cheese, and it did not disappoint! The Roasted Broccoli was especially delicious, and overall Dig had some great healthy options to choose from. Service was quick and easy too! Definitely would recommend.
Had a great experience ‚Äî great portions and overall quality for the price. Had to wait a few minutes for extra protein but was comp‚Äôd with 2 free beverages in return. Highly recommend
Pretty expensive but really tasty food, we came when there wasn‚Äôt much of a line and we got our food pretty fast. Food was pretty and had really nice flavor, but $15 hurts my pocket for a bowl ngl

A great selection of healthy options that taste delicious. Dig Inn offers reasonable sized portions of high quality for a justified price. Would highly recommend the kitchen sink cookies and the Ginger Lemonade üëå‚Ä¶

Super Great Customer Service!!!
Food is always delicious and fresh.
Tamia and Carla did a great Job explaining the food ingredients.
Great fresh food! Perfect for a light lunch. Very friendly service. Was recommended from friends and totally worth it :)

It's unfortunate that the quality of my food and level of service did not meet my expectations the last couple of visits to this location. Not sure if it was because it was so close to closing time when the staff may have been tired but nonetheless it was a poor experience. This was my fish I was not able to eat it.
